cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a deep learning model for text classification that focuses on modeling context information. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also extensively evaluates the proposed method on benchmark datasets, indicating a focus on machine learning and evaluation, which suggests the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as likely options. Finally, the paper deals with text classification, which is a task related to information retrieval, suggesting cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as a possible sub-category.
